Popular children’s cartoon “Dora The Explorer” is getting a live action remake. During the broadcast of the 2019 Kids’ Choice Awards, Nickelodeon Films and Paramount Pictures shared the first trailer for Dora and the Lost City of Gold. The two-and-a-half minute preview follows Dora as she migrates from the jungle away from her parents to live with her cousin Diego and his family in the city.
And as if the transition wasn’t enough, Dora and several of her classmates must eventually come together to solve the mystery of a lost Inca civilization and are tasked with saving Dora’s parents. The film was directed by James Bobin and stars Isabela Moner as Dora. Jeffrey Wahlberg will play Dora’s cousin Diego, while Danny Trejo will voice the character of Dora’s monkey sidekick Boots. The movie is set to hit theaters on the 2nd of August 2019. Watch the full trailer for “Dora and the Lost City of Gold” via YouTube below;